---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Support — Guitar Tab Reader" description="Get help with the Guitar Tab Reader app.">
  <Header />

  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Support</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600">Need help with Guitar Tab Reader? We're here for you.</p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Contact Us</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">For any questions, issues, or feedback, reach out to us at:</p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          <a href="mailto:support@guitartabreader.app" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">support@guitartabreader.app</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Common Questions</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-6">
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-medium text-gray-900">Which file types are supported?</h3>
            <p class="mt-1">Guitar Tab Reader opens Guitar Pro files including .gp, .gpx, .gp5, .gp4, and .gp3. Rendering and playback are powered by the alphaTab engine.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-medium text-gray-900">How do I open a file?</h3>
            <p class="mt-1">Open a file from within the app, or drag and drop it onto the window on desktop. Your files stay on your device and are never uploaded.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-medium text-gray-900">Why is there no sound during playback?</h3>
            <p class="mt-1">Make sure your device volume is up and the track you want to hear is not muted. Some scores have individual tracks muted by default — check the track controls and unmute the parts you want to play.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-medium text-gray-900">Is the app really free?</h3>
            <p class="mt-1">Yes. Guitar Tab Reader is completely free, with no ads, no accounts, no subscriptions, and no tracking.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Bug Reports &amp; Feature Requests</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">Found a bug or have an idea? Email us with a description of the issue, the file that caused it (if applicable), your device or operating system, and the app version. Screenshots or screen recordings are very helpful.</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
